<TITLE> India recall Balaji for Sri Lanka series </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, Feb 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India selectors have recalled Lakshmipathy Balaji to the national squad after three years to replace injured fellow paceman Munaf Patel in the current one-day series in Sri Lanka. Patel has been ruled out due to a groin injury and Balaji will reach Colombo ahead of Tuesday's third game, the Board of Control for Cricket in India said in a statement. India are 2-0 up in the five-match series. The 27-year-old Balaji has not played for India since August 2005 due to injury but has shown excellent form in domestic games this season
